ean, well-documented, and the tests are focused and passing. 100% pass rate on the relevant test suites (`tests/test_sample_record_skeleton.py` and `tests/test_sample_library.py`).\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe skeleton implementation is solid. The missing fields from `CCS-001` (`pitch_confidence`, `duration_sec`, `presence`, `rms`, `peak`, `transient_density`, `gain_db`) and the `dict[str,float]` type for `mood` are correctly deferred to subsequent subtasks (`Zb`, `Zc`, `Zd`).\n\n**Candidate Hardening:** The recurring hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` and `FirstBootAnnouncer` were verified to be unrelated to the `SampleRecord` dataclass scope. Pre-existing startup wiring in `daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py` already addresses these concerns.\n"}}
